f=Executive Office/vista/custom/roadmap-sync/SKILL.md · in=roadmap-sync detects drift between committed quarterly roadmap what actually shipping, sprint sprint instead reporting lateness, proposes what about it: cut, defer, accelerate. Built scratch against catalog entry; drift math deliberately plain (sprints late projected committed) invented scoring, deterministic part (slip computation, classification, table rendering) lives `scripts/roadmap_sync.py`. · p=Plans drift quietly. roadmap item slips one sprint rarely announces itself; time slipped three, quarter unrecoverable. skill gives vista repeatable checkpoint surfaces slippage early, classifies consistently, converts flagged item decision-ready recommendation marcus rather status report nobody acts on. · wu=Triggers: "roadmap drift," "are plan," "sync roadmap," "sprint review roadmap," "what's slipping," recurring cadence (typically once sprint, after sprint output known). for: sequencing what goes roadmap (that's `rice-prioritization`), grading quarter-end outcomes (that's `okr-quality-checker`). · st:/ Protocol=`Establish baseline (committed roadmap + sprint targets — if none exists, stop) \· -> Collect actuals per item (sprint output, status — never assumed) \· -> Compute drift via scripts/roadmap_sync.py (slip = projected − committed sprint) \· -> Classify: on-track (≤0) / watch (1) / flagged (≥2, configurable) \· -> Propose per flagged item: cut / defer / accelerate, with trade-offs` · h3:Phase Establish Baseline=Load committed roadmap: item's name, committed completion sprint (or quarter position), available which NSM input feeds (see `north-star-metric`) RICE score (see `rice-prioritization`). committed roadmap sprint targets exists, stop say so: nothing sync against. Route operator `rice-prioritization` sequence one first. reconstruct "probably intended" roadmap memory. · h3:Phase Collect Actuals=item, get current state: projected completion sprint (from team's estimate observable progress) optionally percent complete. Actuals come operator configured delivery source never estimated vista fill gap. item's actual state unknown, list **unknown**, on-track. · h3:Phase Compute Drift=`python scripts/roadmap_sync.py <input.json>              # markdown drift table \· python scripts/roadmap_sync.py <input.json> --format json  # machine-readable` · h3:Phase Compute Drift=Build input JSON schema top `scripts/roadmap_sync.py` run: script computes, item: `slip projected_sprint committed_sprint`, classifies status, sorts flagged items first. flag threshold defaults **2 sprints** (catalog value) configurable input file changing operator decision, vista's. · h3:Phase 4 — Classify=**on-track** slip, **watch** slip action proposed yet; named next sync run compares against it., **flagged** slip threshold (default 2). flagged item get Phase recommendation., **unknown** reliable actual. Treated class; unknown data problem fix, pass. · h3:Phase 4 — Classify=Percent complete, provided, reported alongside context scored thresholded (no invented pace formula; see Principles). · h3:Phase Propose Options=flagged item, lay out three options honest trade-offs: · h3:Phase Propose Options=**Cut** remove quarter. State what lost: which NSM input stops fed, what downstream items depended it., **Defer** move next quarter explicitly. State cost carrying it: stale context, blocked dependents, deferral without named new slot slow-motion cut., **Accelerate** add resources descope neighbors recover date. State what gets starved pay (name specific items losing capacity). · h3:Phase Propose Options=item RICE score named NSM input, use them recommendation ("lowest RICE score flagged set cheapest cut" "feeds top NSM input accelerate before cutting"). neither exists, say recommendation judgment-based. · h3:Phase 6 — Route=drift table plus per-item recommendations **marcus** actual cut/defer/accelerate decision vista recommends, never decides. configured delivery-owner contact (see `operational/agent/` config built; until then, operator directly) notified flagged items delivery side isn't surprised escalation. · of=`## Roadmap Sync: [scope / sprint N of M / date] \·  \· \| Item \| Committed \| Projected \| Slip \| % done \| Status \| NSM input \| RICE \| \· \|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| \· [from script output, flagged first]` · pr=**No invented pace math.** Slip sprints one metric; percent complete context, score. richer drift formula ever wanted, that's logical-layer discussion (rule 0.6), something improvise here., **Unknown on-track.** Missing actuals surfaced their class, never defaulted green., **Recommend, don't override.** Cut/defer/accelerate marcus's call; vista's job making call easy well-informed., **Every flagged item gets options, red cell.** drift report without recommendations status report; skill exists that., **Deferral named cost, free pass.** "Defer" without committed new slot flagged implicit cut., **Same threshold run.** flag threshold set config changed deliberately adjusted mid-quarter make report look better. · f=committed roadmap stop Phase route `rice-prioritization`., Actuals unavailable items produce table anyway unknowns dominating, make closing data gap top recommendation., Python unavailable compute slip projected committed manually item using classification; flag run wasn't script-computed (audit trail difference)., RICE scores NSM inputs established omit columns, state recommendations judgment-based, note which upstream skill strengthen them. · b:with Other vista Skills=`rice-prioritization` decides what goes roadmap; roadmap-sync monitors whether decided roadmap actually happening. accelerate/cut decision reshuffles remaining capacity trigger RICE re-run., `north-star-metric` supplies which NSM input item feeds main tiebreaker between cutting accelerating flagged item., `okr-quality-checker` grades outcomes quarter end; roadmap-sync in-quarter early warning makes grades less surprising., Escalation target **marcus** (okr-cascade owns quarterly objectives roadmap serves); vista finalize cut/defer/accelerate calls.